               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>On foll. 132, 132v are added four hexameters about health, beg. 'Si vis post cenam' (15th cent.): a copy of 'the Answer of the Deanry of Cycestre' (<orgName key="org_193">Chichester</orgName>) in 1535 to a demand for a money contribution granted by Convocation to the king: five sets of humorous verses, one being the story of four Oxford scholars invited to write an epigram on a pair of buckets in a well.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
